  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "CVT oil pressure measurement"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Garage jacks, rigid racks, and lifts should be securely applied in place.",
        "Before performing the inspection, check the DTCs and, if DTCs are displayed, diagnose the malfunction of the displayed DTCs.",
        "This inspection should not be performed continuously for more than 10 seconds.",
        "Do not operate the select lever with the engine running at high rpm.",
        "Be very careful when turning the wheels.",
        "When connecting the oil pressure gauge, be sure to connect it securely so that no dust or other debris can enter through the oil pressure sensing hole.",
        "VSA must be turned off.",
        "If the wheels are idling, VSA DTCs may be detected. If a DTC is detected, use HDS to clear the DTC."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Engine Warming up"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Warm up the radiator fan until it operates twice. Place the vehicle on a level surface and stop the engine."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Lift Set",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "G000319",
          "label": "Lift Set",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Left side front splash guard removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000849",
          "label": "Left side front splash guard removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Transmission Fluid Level Check",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000542",
          "label": "Transmission Fluid Level Check",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. HDS Connection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "518_5.0_jpn_11582133_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Connect HDS to the data link coupler (A) on the left side of the driver's seat."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. Drive pulley pressure Measurement"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "518_5.0_jpn_11582134_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "518_5.0_jpn_11582135_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Drive pulley pressure measurement"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install the oil pressure gauge (07406-0020005) in the drive pulley pressure sensing hole (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Measuring pressure",
            "header": true
          },
          {
            "text": "Standard value kPa (kgf/cm) 2 ）",
            "header": true
          }
        ],
        [
          {
            "text": "Drive pulley pressure"
          },
          {
            "text": "594－986（6.1－10.1）"
          }
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "rows": [
        [
          {
            "text": "Measuring pressure",
            "header": true
          },
          {
